{{medical}}
[[Image:Taxol.svg|thumb]]（Taxol）是衍生自[[短叶红豆杉|紫杉树]]的天然产物<ref name="CRC Press">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=fOfFNOMkks8C&pg=PA5 |title=Biologically Active Natural Products: Pharmaceuticals | vauthors = Cutler S, Cutler HG | year = 2000 | publisher = CRC Press | page = 5 | isbn = 978-0-8493-1887-0 }}</ref>。]]

'''天然产物'''（{{lang-en|Natural product}}）是在自然界中由活生物产生的那些通常具有药理学或生物学活性的化学物质，可被用于药学上的[[药物研发|药物研发]]与[[药物设计|药物设计]]；而'''天然产物化学'''是运用现代化科学理论与方法研究[[天然药物|天然药物]]中[[化学|化学]]成分的一门学科。其研究内容包括各类天然药物的化学成分（主要是生理活性成分或药效成分）的结构特点、物理化学性质、提取分离方法以及主要类型化学成分的结构鉴定与[[生物合成|生物合成]]途径等。

在[[有机化学|有机化学]]领域，天然产物的定义通常限于从[[初级代谢产物|初级代谢]]的或[[次级代谢产物|次级代谢]]的途径产生的天然来源分离的纯化的[[有机化合物|有机化合物]]<ref name = "Hanson_2003">{{cite book  | author = Hanson JR | title = Natural Products: the Secondary Metabolite | date = 2003 | publisher = Royal Society of Chemistry | location = Cambridge | isbn = 0-85404-490-6 | quote = Natural products are organic compounds that are formed by living systems. }}</ref>。在[[药物化学|药物化学]]领域，定义往往进一步局限于[[次级代谢产物|次级代谢产物]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Natural Products|url=http://www.medilexicon.com/medicaldictionary.php?t=72549|accessdate=|author=|date=|format=|work=[[Stedman's_Medical_Dictionary|Stedman's Medical Dictionary]]|publisher=Lippincott Williams & Wilkins|language=en|quote=Natural products: naturally occurring compounds that are end products of secondary metabolism; often, they are unique compounds for particular organisms or classes of organisms.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803091030/http://www.medilexicon.com/medicaldictionary.php?t=72549|archive-date=2016-08-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | vauthors = Williams DA, Lemke TL | title = Foye's Principles of Medicinal Chemistry | date = 2002 | edition = 5th | publisher = Lippincott Williams  Wilkins | location = Philadelphia | isbn = 0-683-30737-1 | page = 25 | chapter = Chapter 1: Natural Products | chapterurl = https://books.google.com/books?id=KGLF4ZudTyAC&lpg=PP1&dq=isbn%3A0683307371&pg=PA25#v=onepage&q=Table%201.1&f=false | quote = Natural product: A single chemical compound that occurs naturally.  This term is typically used to refer to an organic compound of limited distribution in nature (often called secondary metabolites). | access-date = 2017-08-04 | archive-date = 2016-05-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160503011639/https://books.google.com/books?id=KGLF4ZudTyAC&lpg=PP1&dq=isbn%3A0683307371&pg=PA25#v=onepage&q=Table%201.1&f=false | dead-url = no }}</ref>。次级代谢产物不是生存必需品，而是为生物提供了演化的优势<ref name="pmid1612430">{{cite journal | vauthors = Maplestone RA, Stone MJ, Williams DH | title = The evolutionary role of secondary metabolites--a review | journal = Gene | volume = 115 | issue = 1–2 | pages = 151–7 | date = June 1992 | pmid = 1612430 | doi = 10.1016/0378-1119(92)90553-2 }}</ref>。许多次级代谢产物是[[細胞毒性|细胞毒性]]的，并且通过进化已经被选择和被优化，用作对抗猎物，捕食者和竞争生物的“化学战争”药剂<ref name="pmid18762775">{{cite journal | vauthors = Hunter P | title = Harnessing Nature's wisdom. Turning to Nature for inspiration and avoiding her follies | journal = EMBO Reports | volume = 9 | issue = 9 | pages = 838–40 | date = September 2008 | pmid = 18762775 | pmc = 2529361 | doi = 10.1038/embor.2008.160 }}</ref>。

天然产物有时具有治疗疾病的传统药物的治疗效果，产生作为{{le|药物发现|Drug discovery}}的[[先导化合物|先导化合物]]的活性成分的知识<ref name="Li_2009">{{cite journal|title=Drug discovery and natural products: end of an era or an endless frontier?|author=|url=|date=July 2009|journal=Science|issue=5937|doi=10.1126/science.1168243|others=|year=|volume=325|page=|pages=161–5|language=en|pmid=19589993|vauthors=Li JW, Vederas JC}}</ref>。虽然天然产品启发了许多[[美国食品和药物管理局|美国食品和药物管理局]]批准的药物，但天然来源的药物开发已经受到制药公司的减低的关注，部分原因是获取和供应的不可靠，[[知识产权|知识产权]]问题，组成的季节性或环境变异性，以及由于[[灭绝|灭绝]]率上升而失去来源<ref name=Li_2009/>。

